000100 IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.
000200 PROGRAM-ID. pi-calc.
000300 AUTHOR. LodoreStiffler.
000400* This program calculates hex digits of pi sequentially using the
000401* Bailey-Borwein-Plouffe formula. Each digit at position n is
000402* computed directly via frac(16^n * pi), without deriving earlier
000403* digits. Precision is bounded by 18 fractional decimals of
000404* storage (~12-14 reliable hex digits); beyond that, errors
000405* accumulate in the running mod-1 sums.
000410*~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
000420 DATA DIVISION.
000421*~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
000430 WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.
000440 01  INPUT-VARS.
000450     05  N                PIC 9(6).
000460 01  SUM-VARS.
000470     05  S1               PIC S9(3)V9(18) VALUE 0.
000480     05  S4               PIC S9(3)V9(18) VALUE 0.
000490     05  S5               PIC S9(3)V9(18) VALUE 0.
000500     05  S6               PIC S9(3)V9(18) VALUE 0.
000510     05  PI-FRAC          PIC S9(3)V9(18).
000520     05  HEX-DIGIT        PIC 9(2).
000530 01  SERIES-VARS.
000540     05  K                PIC 9(8).
000550     05  DENOM            PIC 9(8).
000560     05  POWER-EXP        PIC 9(8).
000570     05  MOD-RESULT       PIC 9(18).
000571     05  TEMP-BASE        PIC 9(18).
000572     05  TEMP-PROD        PIC 9(18).
000580     05  TERM             PIC S9(3)V9(18).
000581     05  DIGIT-POS        PIC 9(8).
000582     05  J-OFFSET         PIC 9(2).
000583     05  PARTIAL-SUM      PIC S9(3)V9(18).
000584     05  POW-FRAC         PIC S9(3)V9(18).
000585 01  OUTPUT-VARS.
000586     05  HEX-CHARS        PIC X(16) VALUE "0123456789ABCDEF".
000587     05  HEX-CH           PIC X.
000588     05  HEX-IDX          PIC 9(2).
000589 01  BIGNUM-SCALARS.
000590     05  MAX-DIG          PIC 9(4) VALUE 250.
000591     05  I                PIC 9(4).
000592     05  CARRY            PIC 9(3).
000593     05  TEMP-VAL         PIC 9(4).
000594     05  TRIM-LEN         PIC 9(4).
000595 01  PI-DEC-GRP.
000596     05  PI-DEC-DIG       PIC 9 OCCURS 250 TIMES.
000597 01  POW-GRP.
000598     05  POW-DIG          PIC 9 OCCURS 250 TIMES.
000599*~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
000600 PROCEDURE DIVISION.
000610*~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
000620 MAIN.
000630     DISPLAY "Enter the number of digits of pi to calculate(1M): "
000631         WITH NO ADVANCING.
000640     ACCEPT N.
000645     MOVE 1 TO POW-DIG(1).
000650     DISPLAY "3." WITH NO ADVANCING.
000660     PERFORM COMPUTE-DIGIT
000670         VARYING DIGIT-POS FROM 0 BY 1 UNTIL DIGIT-POS >= N.
000680     DISPLAY " ".
000681     COMPUTE TRIM-LEN = FUNCTION INTEGER(N * 6 / 5) + 2.
000682     IF TRIM-LEN > MAX-DIG
000683         MOVE MAX-DIG TO TRIM-LEN
000684     END-IF.
000685     DISPLAY "  = 3." PI-DEC-GRP(1:TRIM-LEN).
000690     STOP RUN.
000700*
000710 COMPUTE-DIGIT.
000720     MOVE 1 TO J-OFFSET
000730     PERFORM SUM-SERIES
000740     MOVE PARTIAL-SUM TO S1.
000750     MOVE 4 TO J-OFFSET
000760     PERFORM SUM-SERIES
000770     MOVE PARTIAL-SUM TO S4.
000780     MOVE 5 TO J-OFFSET
000790     PERFORM SUM-SERIES
000800     MOVE PARTIAL-SUM TO S5.
000810     MOVE 6 TO J-OFFSET
000820     PERFORM SUM-SERIES
000830     MOVE PARTIAL-SUM TO S6.
000840     COMPUTE PI-FRAC = 4 * S1 - 2 * S4 - S5 - S6
000850     SUBTRACT FUNCTION INTEGER(PI-FRAC) FROM PI-FRAC
000860     COMPUTE HEX-DIGIT = FUNCTION INTEGER(PI-FRAC * 16)
000861     PERFORM DIV-POW-BY-16
000862     PERFORM ADD-HEX-POW-TO-PI
000870     COMPUTE HEX-IDX = HEX-DIGIT + 1
000880     MOVE HEX-CHARS(HEX-IDX:1) TO HEX-CH
000890     DISPLAY HEX-CH WITH NO ADVANCING.
000900*
000910*  Accumulates S_j = sum_{k=0..inf} 16^(n-k) / (8k+j), mod 1.
000920 SUM-SERIES.
000930     MOVE 0 TO PARTIAL-SUM
000940     PERFORM FINITE-TERM
000950         VARYING K FROM 0 BY 1 UNTIL K > DIGIT-POS
000960     MOVE 1 TO POW-FRAC
000970     COMPUTE K = DIGIT-POS + 1
000980     PERFORM 30 TIMES
000990         COMPUTE POW-FRAC = POW-FRAC / 16
001000         COMPUTE DENOM = 8 * K + J-OFFSET
001010         COMPUTE PARTIAL-SUM = PARTIAL-SUM + POW-FRAC / DENOM
001020         ADD 1 TO K
001030     END-PERFORM
001040     SUBTRACT FUNCTION INTEGER(PARTIAL-SUM) FROM PARTIAL-SUM.
001050*
001060 FINITE-TERM.
001070     COMPUTE DENOM = 8 * K + J-OFFSET
001080     COMPUTE POWER-EXP = DIGIT-POS - K
001090     PERFORM MOD-POW-16
001100     COMPUTE TERM = MOD-RESULT / DENOM
001110     COMPUTE PARTIAL-SUM = PARTIAL-SUM + TERM
001120     SUBTRACT FUNCTION INTEGER(PARTIAL-SUM) FROM PARTIAL-SUM.
001130*
001140*  Binary modular exponentiation: MOD-RESULT = 16^POWER-EXP mod DENOM.
001150 MOD-POW-16.
001160     IF DENOM = 1
001170         MOVE 0 TO MOD-RESULT
001180     ELSE
001190         MOVE 1 TO MOD-RESULT
001200         MOVE 16 TO TEMP-BASE
001210         COMPUTE TEMP-BASE = FUNCTION REM(TEMP-BASE, DENOM)
001220         PERFORM UNTIL POWER-EXP = 0
001230             IF FUNCTION REM(POWER-EXP, 2) = 1
001240                 COMPUTE TEMP-PROD = MOD-RESULT * TEMP-BASE
001250                 COMPUTE MOD-RESULT =
001260                     FUNCTION REM(TEMP-PROD, DENOM)
001270             END-IF
001280             COMPUTE POWER-EXP =
001290                 FUNCTION INTEGER(POWER-EXP / 2)
001300             COMPUTE TEMP-PROD = TEMP-BASE * TEMP-BASE
001310             COMPUTE TEMP-BASE =
001320                 FUNCTION REM(TEMP-PROD, DENOM)
001330         END-PERFORM
001340     END-IF.
001350*
001360*  BIGNUM: POW := POW / 16, in place. POW-DIG(1) is the units
001370*  digit; POW-DIG(i) for i > 1 is the 10^-(i-1) place.
001380 DIV-POW-BY-16.
001390     MOVE 0 TO CARRY
001400     PERFORM VARYING I FROM 1 BY 1 UNTIL I > MAX-DIG
001410         COMPUTE TEMP-VAL = CARRY * 10 + POW-DIG(I)
001420         DIVIDE TEMP-VAL BY 16
001430             GIVING POW-DIG(I) REMAINDER CARRY
001440     END-PERFORM.
001450*
001460*  BIGNUM: PI-DEC := PI-DEC + HEX-DIGIT * POW, right-to-left.
001470*  PI-DEC-DIG(j) is the 10^-j place; POW-DIG(j+1) shares that
001480*  place (POW index 1 is 10^0).
001490 ADD-HEX-POW-TO-PI.
001500     MOVE 0 TO CARRY
001510     PERFORM VARYING I FROM MAX-DIG BY -1 UNTIL I < 1
001520         IF I = MAX-DIG
001530             COMPUTE TEMP-VAL = PI-DEC-DIG(I) + CARRY
001540         ELSE
001550             COMPUTE TEMP-VAL = PI-DEC-DIG(I) + CARRY
001560                 + HEX-DIGIT * POW-DIG(I + 1)
001570         END-IF
001580         DIVIDE TEMP-VAL BY 10
001590             GIVING CARRY REMAINDER PI-DEC-DIG(I)
001600     END-PERFORM.
